<p align="center"><font color="#0E024D" face="Arial"><strong>PLAYER SUBMITTED STRATEGY</strong></font></p>
<div align="center"><center>

  <div align="center"><center><table border="0" width="90%">
    <tr>
      <td>
      <center><font face="Arial"><strong><b><font color="#800000">HOW TO GET FROM 1-24 (DARK ELF)</b></font> - <small>Soulidus Do'Urden, Veeshan</small></strong></font><font face="Arial"></center>
<div align="center"><center>
<table border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" width="80%">
  <tr>
    <td>
    <small><hr size="1" color="#C0C0C0"><P>
    <P>So you start out as your new necromancer. What do you do now? Well obviously find you guild. The necromancer guild is located in Neriak- 3rd Gate. Head along the left wall and eventaully you will come to it. Ok so you get your robe and decide its time to fight. Find your way out and head to the Nektulos Forest. Head onto the pathway and look for snakes (moss) and decaying skeletons. When you hit level 2(wont take you that long) start killing black wolves and fire beetles. I recommend killing as many fire bettles as possible till level 5 due to the fact that their eyes sell for about 2silver and 2-4 copper which is great for that level. 
<P>Get to level 8 and then head to East Commons. I suggest maybe grouping to take out Orcs and perhaps soloing giant scarabs. You may have to group until level 10. at level 11 take out Lions, Lionesses and Young Kodiaks.
<P>When you finally get to level 12 go to sister island. Take the boat from Freeport and zone to Ocean of Tears. Be on the right side of the boat and you will eventually have to jump off before getting to the docks. If you wait till the docks and try to get off, you will get KOS-ed(Killed on Sight) by the Wood Elves. When you jump off and get to land simply find a sister, con her and if you think you can take her, start off with a nice heatblood followed by some lifedraws. Make sure you have your pet attacking and help him melee from time to time. Keep doing this till you hit 16.
<P>Level 16, in my opinion offers the best variety of spells I have seen so far. Head straight to oasis! I suggest taking on the crocs. They do not group fight so you can be killing a croc and another one will just walk on by. The strategy i used contained the following spells.<P>
1) First start out with a Engulfing Darkness. This will slow the target down giving you time for step 2.<br>
2) Heat Blood<br>
3)Send Pet<br>
4) Heart Flutter. These DoT's get the croc pretty mad and may decide to turn on you instead of your pet. Thats wear the most important spell comes in.<br>
5) Fear! Yes...Fear! Fear the croc and he will SLOWLY run away because of the darkness. Life draw him, melee him, do whatever it takes. If Fear wears off, keep using it. <p>
This strategy worked great and i leveled to 18 quickly.<P>
Ah you have reached 18, have you. Head to Lake Rathetear. I leveled from 18 to 20 in 3 days and I only play about 4 hours a day, maybe not even that. Head to a nice 1 or 2 spawn (2spawns...I suggest asking someone to share it with you.) After every spawn use only these 3 spells...Heat Blood, Heart Flutter and Life Draw in that order. The monster will get pissed and definatly come after you. Try to time your casts and continuously cast Life Draw after that. After each kill I recommend using Dark Pact to drain HP for mana. this works out great and you can always just lifedraw your Hp back.<P>
Oh so you get to level 20. Keep killing in Lake Rathe...doing the same strategy I told you before. You get a new spell in the Life Draw line of spells...Siphon Life. This spell does about 65 damage. You also get allure of death (same as dark pact, just more HP for more mana) Harm Shield is also a great spell. If you run out of mana simply cast this and the monster cannot damage you for a bit of time. During this period you cannot cast spells.<P>
At Level 22 you may want to try to group to take out DW Goblin Pets. Those little doggies love to group attack so be careful. You can also stick to killing aviaks. <P>
Using this strategy helped me level from 1-24 very much. Hope you enjoy it as well.<P>
Good Luck to you! If you have any questions or comments feel free to e-mail me at klepore1@tampabay.rr.com<P>
Thanks,<BR>
Soulidus Do'Urden

    
		
    </small></font></p>
